        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 4:20PM PDT until July 1 at 4:45PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM PDT, an area of showers and isolated thunderstorms was
moving through the Las Vegas Valley moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs and trees. Visibilities may be
reduced to less that 1/2 mile at times.

Locations impacted include...
Las Vegas, Henderson, North Las Vegas, Anthem, The Strip, Nellis AFB,
East Las Vegas, Sam Boyd Stadium, The Motor Speedway, Southern
Highlands, Aliante, Lake Las Vegas, Spring Valley, Green Valley,
Enterprise, Fremont Street, Paradise, Lone Mountain, Centennial
Hills, and Mountains Edge.

This includes Interstate 15 in Nevada between mile markers 22 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
